<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Tali — Nike Melbourne Marathon 10k 2026</title>
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  :root {
    --bg: #ffffff; --bg-secondary: #f7f7f5; --bg-tertiary: #f0efeb;
    --text-primary: #1a1a18; --text-secondary: #6b6b63; --text-tertiary: #9a9a92;
    --border: rgba(0,0,0,0.12); --border-mid: rgba(0,0,0,0.18);
    --teal: #1D9E75; --teal-light: #E1F5EE; --teal-dark: #0F6E56;
    --blue-light: #E6F1FB; --blue-dark: #185FA5; --blue-mid: #0C447C;
    --amber-light: #FAEEDA; --amber-dark: #854F0B;
    --coral-light: #FAECE7; --coral-dark: #993C1D;
    --purple-light: #EEEDFE; --purple-dark: #3C3489;
    --green-light: #EAF3DE; --green-dark: #27500A;
    --radius-sm: 8px; --radius-md: 12px; --radius-lg: 16px;
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    :root {
      --bg: #1c1c1a; --bg-secondary: #252523; --bg-tertiary: #2e2e2b;
      --text-primary: #f0efea; --text-secondary: #a0a098; --text-tertiary: #6b6b63;
      --border: rgba(255,255,255,0.10); --border-mid: rgba(255,255,255,0.16);
      --teal-light: #085041; --teal-dark: #9FE1CB;
      --blue-light: #0C447C; --blue-dark: #B5D4F4; --blue-mid: #B5D4F4;
      --amber-light: #633806; --amber-dark: #FAC775;
      --coral-light: #712B13; --coral-dark: #F5C4B3;
      --purple-light: #3C3489; --purple-dark: #CECBF6;
      --green-light: #27500A; --green-dark: #C0DD97;
    }
  }
  body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', system-ui, sans-serif; background: var(--bg-tertiary); color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.5; padding: 1.5rem 1rem; min-height: 100vh; }
  .container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }

  /* Hero */
  .hero { background: var(--bg); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1.25rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .avatar { width: 60px; height: 60px; border-radius: 50%; background: #E05A2B; color: #fff; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .hero-title { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1.2; }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 4px; }
  .badges { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .badge { font-size: 12px; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 20px; font-weight: 500; }
  .badge-teal { background: var(--teal-light); color: var(--teal-dark); }
  .badge-blue { background: var(--blue-light); color: var(--blue-dark); }
  .badge-amber { background: var(--amber-light); color: var(--amber-dark); }
  .badge-coral { background: var(--coral-light); color: var(--coral-dark); }

  /* Stats */
  .stats { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(145px, 1fr)); gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .stat { background: var(--bg); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 1rem 1.25rem; }
  .stat-label { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .stat-val { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .stat-sub { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-top: 2px; }

  /* Tabs */
  .tabs { display: flex; gap: 4px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .tab { padding: 7px 16px; border-radius: 20px; font-size: 13px; cursor: pointer; border: 0.5px solid var(--border-mid); background: transparent; color: var(--text-secondary); transition: all 0.15s; font-family: inherit; }
  .tab:hover { background: var(--bg-secondary); color: var(--text-primary); }
  .tab.active { background: #E05A2B; border-color: #E05A2B; color: #fff; }

  .panel { display: none; }
  .panel.active { display: block; }

  /* Shared */
  .card { background: var(--bg); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 1.25rem; }
  .card-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .section-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .grid-2 { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .grid-auto { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; }
  @media (max-width: 600px) { .grid-2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  hr { border: none; border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border); margin: 1.5rem 0; }

  /* Philosophy */
  .phil-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 10px; }
  .phil-item { display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: flex-start; background: var(--bg); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 1rem; }
  .phil-icon { font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; line-height: 1; }
  .phil-text strong { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .phil-text span { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }

  /* Week struct */
  .week-struct { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 12px; }
  .week-struct th { padding: 8px; background: var(--bg-secondary); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); text-align: center; }
  .week-struct td { padding: 8px; border: 0.5px solid var(--border); text-align: center; vertical-align: top; font-size: 12px; }

  /* Pace */
  .pace-card { background: var(--bg); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 1rem; }
  .pace-type { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 6px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .pace-num { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .pace-unit { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .pace-bar { height: 3px; border-radius: 2px; margin: 8px 0; }
  .pace-desc { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }

  /* Phase */
  .phase-card { background: var(--bg); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 1.25rem; }
  .phase-tag { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 10px; display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .tag-f { background: var(--teal-light); color: var(--teal-dark); }
  .tag-b { background: var(--blue-light); color: var(--blue-dark); }
  .tag-t { background: var(--coral-light); color: var(--coral-dark); }
  .phase-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 3px; }
  .phase-dates { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .phase-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .phase-goals { border-top: 0.5px solid var(--border); padding-top: 10px; list-style: none; }
  .phase-goals li { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); padding: 2px 0 2px 16px; position: relative; line-height: 1.5; }
  .phase-goals li::before { content: '→'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: #E05A2B; }

  /* Schedule table */
  .sched-outer { overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
  .sched { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 12px; min-width: 820px; }
  .sched th { padding: 8px; text-align: left; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); background: var(--bg-secondary); border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border); white-space: nowrap; }
  .sched td { padding: 8px; vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border); line-height: 1.4; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .sched tr:hover td { filter: brightness(0.97); }
  .week-cell { font-weight: 600; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 12px; }
  .week-date { font-size: 10px; color: var(--text-secondary); font-weight: 400; }
  .km-cell { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-secondary); white-space: nowrap; font-weight: 600; }

  /* Cell colours — identical to Tegan's plan */
  .cr { background: var(--bg-secondary); color: var(--text-secondary); font-style: italic; }
  .ch { background: var(--blue-light); color: var(--blue-mid); }
  .ce { background: var(--green-light); color: var(--green-dark); }
  .cq { background: var(--amber-light); color: var(--amber-dark); }
  .cl { background: var(--coral-light); color: var(--coral-dark); }
  .cs { background: var(--purple-light); color: var(--purple-dark); }
  .cx { background: #E05A2B; color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }

  .phase-row td { background: var(--bg-tertiary); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; padding: 6px 8px; border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border); }

  /* Legend */
  .legend { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .leg { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .leg-dot { width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 3px; }

  /* Fixture table */
  .ftable { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; }
  .ftable th { padding: 8px 10px; text-align: left; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); background: var(--bg-secondary); border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border); white-space: nowrap; }
  .ftable td { padding: 8px 10px; border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border); color: var(--text-primary); font-size: 13px; }
  .ftable tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .ftable tr:hover td { background: var(--bg-secondary); }
  .pill-sat { background: var(--blue-light); color: var(--blue-mid); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; }
  .pill-sun { background: var(--amber-light); color: var(--amber-dark); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; }
  .pill-bye { background: var(--bg-secondary); color: var(--text-tertiary); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; }
  .pill-fin { background: var(--coral-light); color: var(--coral-dark); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; }
  .imp-note { font-size: 12px; color: var(--amber-dark); font-style: italic; }

  /* Strength */
  .scard { background: var(--bg); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 1rem; }
  .s-cat { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--purple-dark); margin-bottom: 8px; padding-bottom: 6px; border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border); }
  .scard ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .scard li { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-secondary); padding: 3px 0 3px 14px; position: relative; line-height: 1.4; }
  .scard li::before { content: '·'; position: absolute; left: 3px; color: #E05A2B; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1; top: 2px; }

  /* Notes */
  .note-card { background: var(--bg); border: 0.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 1.25rem; }
  .note-card-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; }
  .note-card-title .dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: #E05A2B; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .note-card p, .note-card li { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
  .note-card ul { padding-left: 16px; }
  .note-card li { padding: 2px 0; }
  .note-section { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .note-section-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border); }

  /* Boxes */
  .highlight-box { background: var(--teal-light); border: 0.5px solid var(--teal); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 1rem 1.25rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .highlight-box p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--teal-dark); line-height: 1.6; }
  .warning-box { background: var(--amber-light); border: 0.5px solid #EF9F27; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); padding: 1rem 1.25rem; margin-top: 1rem; }
  .warning-box p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--amber-dark); line-height: 1.6; }
  strong { font-weight: 600; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="avatar">T</div>
    <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
      <div class="hero-title">Tali — Nike Melbourne Marathon 10k 2026</div>
      <div class="hero-sub">19-week training plan · 1 June → 11 October 2026 · HV Womens Premier League Reserves — Hawthorn</div>
      <div class="badges">
        <span class="badge badge-teal">Goal: sub 40:00</span>
        <span class="badge badge-blue">Current est: 42:30</span>
        <span class="badge badge-amber">HV WPL Reserves — Hawthorn</span>
        <span class="badge badge-coral">2→3 runs + 1 strength / week</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STATS -->
  <div class="stats">
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-label">Race date</div><div class="stat-val">11 Oct 2026</div><div class="stat-sub">Nike Melbourne Marathon 10k</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-label">Training weeks</div><div class="stat-val">19 weeks</div><div class="stat-sub">1 Jun → race day</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-label">Goal time</div><div class="stat-val">Sub 40:00</div><div class="stat-sub">4:00/km target pace</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-label">Current est.</div><div class="stat-val">42:30</div><div class="stat-sub">~4:15/km</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-label">Time to find</div><div class="stat-val">2:30</div><div class="stat-sub">~15 sec/km improvement</div></div>
    <div class="stat"><div class="stat-label">3rd run added</div><div class="stat-val">Wk 10</div><div class="stat-sub">From Mon 3 Aug</div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- TABS -->
  <div class="tabs">
    <button class="tab active" onclick="showTab('philosophy',this)">Philosophy</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('paces',this)">Training paces</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('phases',this)">Phases</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('schedule',this)">Full schedule</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('fixtures',this)">Hockey fixtures</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('strength',this)">Strength</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('notes',this)">Anna's notes</button>
  </div>

  <!-- ===================== PHILOSOPHY ===================== -->
  <div id="tab-philosophy" class="panel active">
    <div class="section-title">Training philosophy</div>
    <div class="phil-grid" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
      <div class="phil-item"><div class="phil-icon">🎯</div><div class="phil-text"><strong>One race, one mission</strong><span>Everything in this plan is built around running 10 km at 4:00/km or faster. Short, sharp, and specific — 10k training is high-quality over high-volume.</span></div></div>
      <div class="phil-item"><div class="phil-icon">📈</div><div class="phil-text"><strong>Build the base first</strong><span>Weeks 1–9 use just 2 runs per week to establish the aerobic foundation without burning out. Consistency across 9 weeks beats big early weeks that lead to injury.</span></div></div>
      <div class="phil-item"><div class="phil-icon">🏑</div><div class="phil-text"><strong>Hockey is conditioning</strong><span>Tuesday and Thursday training plus Saturday matches deliver interval-quality cardio, agility, and competitiveness. This is meaningful cross-training — not a compromise.</span></div></div>
      <div class="phil-item"><div class="phil-icon">⚡</div><div class="phil-text"><strong>Quality over quantity</strong><span>With a limited running schedule, every session must earn its place. The long run builds endurance; the Wednesday quality session builds the speed to run sub-4:00/km.</span></div></div>
      <div class="phil-item"><div class="phil-icon">🔁</div><div class="phil-text"><strong>Progressive overload</strong><span>Mileage and intensity increase gradually. A third run is added at week 10 — 8 weeks out — when the aerobic base is ready to absorb more stimulus before taper.</span></div></div>
      <div class="phil-item"><div class="phil-icon">🛡️</div><div class="phil-text"><strong>Arrive healthy</strong><span>A 2:30 improvement over 19 weeks is very achievable. The plan is designed to get there without breaking down — smart progression and one strength session per week.</span></div></div>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <div class="section-title">Weekly structure</div>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-secondary);margin-bottom:1rem;"><strong>Phase 1 (Weeks 1–9):</strong> 2 runs per week — Monday long run + Wednesday strength & easy run. <strong>Phase 2 (Weeks 10–16):</strong> 3 runs — Friday easy run added. <strong>Taper (Weeks 17–19):</strong> volume reduces, sharpness maintained.</p>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto;margin-bottom:1rem;">
      <table class="week-struct">
        <thead><tr><th>Monday</th><th>Tuesday</th><th>Wednesday</th><th>Thursday</th><th>Friday</th><th>Saturday</th><th>Sunday</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="cl">Long run<br><small>Key session</small></td>
            <td class="ch">Hockey training</td>
            <td class="cs">Strength 40 min<br><small>Ph 1 — no run</small></td>
            <td class="ch">Hockey training</td>
            <td class="ce">Easy run<br><small>Run club</small></td>
            <td class="ch">Hockey match</td>
            <td class="cr" style="font-style:italic;">Rest</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="cl">Long run<br><small>Key session</small></td>
            <td class="ch">Hockey training</td>
            <td class="cq">Quality run<br><small>Ph 2+</small></td>
            <td class="ch">Hockey training</td>
            <td class="ce">Easy run<br><small>Ph 2 added</small></td>
            <td class="ch">Hockey match</td>
            <td class="cr" style="font-style:italic;">Rest</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="highlight-box"><p><strong>Week 6 note (Sun 12 Jul — Sunday away game at Doncaster):</strong> The Monday long run falls the day after a Sunday match. That week, the long run shifts to Wednesday and strength moves to Friday. Friday's run club easy run is skipped that week — legs need the day after the Sunday match to recover.</p></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===================== PACES ===================== -->
  <div id="tab-paces" class="panel">
    <div class="section-title">Training pace guide</div>
    <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--text-secondary);margin-bottom:1.25rem;">Based on a sub-40:00 goal (4:00/km) and a current estimated time of 42:30 (~4:15/km). The gap to close is 15 seconds per kilometre — very achievable with consistent 10k-specific training over 19 weeks.</p>
    <div class="grid-auto" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
      <div class="pace-card"><div class="pace-type">Easy / recovery</div><div class="pace-num">5:00–5:30 <span class="pace-unit">/km</span></div><div class="pace-bar" style="background:#9FE1CB;width:25%;"></div><div class="pace-desc">Fully conversational. Z1–Z2 (under 152 bpm). Used on Friday run club sessions and warm-ups. Never skip easy runs — they build the aerobic base that makes fast running possible.</div></div>
      <div class="pace-card"><div class="pace-type">Long run</div><div class="pace-num">4:50–5:15 <span class="pace-unit">/km</span></div><div class="pace-bar" style="background:#63C490;width:38%;"></div><div class="pace-desc">Comfortable and controlled. Z2 (123–152 bpm). Monday sessions. Builds endurance base and time on feet. Longer than race distance to build durability.</div></div>
      <div class="pace-card"><div class="pace-type">Race pace (RP)</div><div class="pace-num">3:58–4:02 <span class="pace-unit">/km</span></div><div class="pace-bar" style="background:#FAC775;width:62%;"></div><div class="pace-desc">Goal 10k effort. Hard but sustainable. Z4 (168–182 bpm). Introduced in quality sessions from week 10. This pace should feel controlled and rehearsed by race day.</div></div>
      <div class="pace-card"><div class="pace-type">Tempo / threshold</div><div class="pace-num">4:10–4:20 <span class="pace-unit">/km</span></div><div class="pace-bar" style="background:#EF9F27;width:72%;"></div><div class="pace-desc">Comfortably hard. Short sentences. Z3–Z4 (153–175 bpm). Used in Wednesday quality sessions — sustained tempo runs and cruise intervals. Raises the lactate threshold, which is the key to running faster for longer.</div></div>
      <div class="pace-card"><div class="pace-type">5k / speed intervals</div><div class="pace-num">3:45–3:55 <span class="pace-unit">/km</span></div><div class="pace-bar" style="background:#D85A30;width:88%;"></div><div class="pace-desc">Hard. One-word answers. Z4–Z5 (178–183+ bpm). Short reps only (400–800m). Used sparingly in peak phase to sharpen top-end speed. Hockey provides some of this naturally.</div></div>
      <div class="pace-card"><div class="pace-type">Hockey training equiv.</div><div class="pace-num">Tempo–interval</div><div class="pace-bar" style="background:#B5D4F4;width:60%;"></div><div class="pace-desc">Sprints, press, and drills count as quality work. On weeks when hockey is very intense, dial back Wednesday quality to a steady easy run instead.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===================== PHASES ===================== -->
  <div id="tab-phases" class="panel">
    <div class="section-title">Training phases</div>
    <div class="grid-2" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
      <div class="phase-card">
        <span class="phase-tag tag-f">Phase 1 — Base</span>
        <div class="phase-name">Aerobic Foundation</div>
        <div class="phase-dates">1 June – 2 August · Weeks 1–9</div>
        <div class="phase-desc">Two runs per week — a Monday long run and a Friday easy run at run club. Wednesday is strength only. The goal is to build a consistent aerobic platform without over-stressing the body alongside hockey. Long runs begin at 6 km and progress gradually to 10 km. Friday runs are relaxed, social, and easy effort — the perfect complement to Monday's key session. Hockey training and Saturday matches provide supplementary conditioning throughout.</div>
        <ul class="phase-goals">
          <li>Establish consistent 2-run weekly habit</li>
          <li>Long run builds from 6 km to 10 km</li>
          <li>Wednesday: strength only (no run)</li>
          <li>Friday: run club easy run (4–5 km)</li>
          <li>Weekly running volume: 10–18 km</li>
          <li>Cutback weeks at weeks 4 and 7</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="phase-card">
        <span class="phase-tag tag-b">Phase 2 — Build</span>
        <div class="phase-name">10k Specific Training</div>
        <div class="phase-dates">3 August – 14 September · Weeks 10–16</div>
